        &lt;article&gt;&lt;![CDATA[&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Activation of the Virtual Agent plugin is required in order to access the configuration page for this task.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can enable Natural Language Understanding (NLU) in your Virtual Agent as a more natural and engaging alternative to keywords to find matching intents and topics. NLU supports intent and entity matching that improves topic discovery and prevents repetitive questions.Â &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From &amp;#39;General Settings&amp;#39; in Virtual Agent, you can use ServiceNow NLU or third-party integrations* including Microsoft LUIS and IBM Watson Assistant integrations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click &amp;#39;Enable NLU&amp;#39; in Virtual Agent, then select an NLU option and save the record. After that, you&amp;#39;ll be able to bind intents and entities to your topics in the Virtual Agent Designer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* In order for your third-party integrations to show up in the list, you&amp;#39;ll need to first define your NLU settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="list-style-position: inside;"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a title="Click here for instructions on integrating with IBM Watson." href="/api/now/v1/context_doc_url/va-watson-nlu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow"&gt;Click here for instructions on integrating with IBM Watson.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a title="Click here for instructions on integrating with Microsoft LUIS." href="/api/now/v1/context_doc_url/va-luis-nlu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow"&gt;Click here for instructions on integrating with Microsoft LUIS.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;]]&gt;&lt;/article&gt;
